        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 4:14AM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 413 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
St. Joe, or 7 miles southeast of Auburn, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
St. Joe, Newville, Concord, Melbern, Edgerton In Williams County,
Blakeslee, Artic, Saint Joe, Edgerton, Edon, Butler, Bryan, and
Spencerville In Dekalb County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
